headline.main: Axis Thrust Into Egypt a Daring Venture, But Damage Caused Is Held Only Slight

lead_paragraph: WITH THE BRITISH ARMY CORPS, in Libya, Nov. 26 (Delayed) -- Orange gun flashes are intermittently flooding the night sky with bursts of light a few miles north of here. They mark the place where British guns, tanks and armored cars are harrying an Axis raiding column on the. frontier of Egypt and Libya.
abstract: Dispatch on Axis thrust into Egypt
